                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="61827" author="adilger" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 19:34:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should be added to the user manual if it isn&apos;t already there. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="61802" author="pjones" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 01:53:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thats good news Herbert. Is there any further action needed or shall we close out this ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="61800" author="hyeung" created="Thu, 4 Jul 2013 00:37:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, ran through the LBA list and they were all unallocated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="61066" author="adilger" created="Sat, 22 Jun 2013 06:44:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you have no partitions on your device, then the LBA (in 512-byte sectors) should be divided by 8 to get 4096-byte filesystem block numbers. Then, use &quot;debugfs -c /dev/XXX&quot; and the &quot;icheck &lt;/p&gt;
{block}
&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;block ...&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot; command to map block numbers to inodes. The mapping from OST inodes to Lustre files is described in &lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.lustre.org/pipermail/lustre-discuss/2013-April/017204.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://lists.lustre.org/pipermail/lustre-discuss/2013-April/017204.html&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It may be in the manual as well (or should be added if it is not already), I didn&apos;t check. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="61063" author="pjones" created="Sat, 22 Jun 2013 05:29:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Niu&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you advise here?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
